      • mergeWorkingSets

        boolean mergeWorkingSets(User user,
                       WorkingSet firstWorkingSet,
                       java.util.List<WorkingSet> wss,
                       boolean deleteRemains)
        Merge two or more WorkingSet objects into WorkingSet firstWorkingSet. Usually the WorkingSet firstWorkingSet will be the currently opened WorkingSet object.

        If a set of WorkingSet objects are merged, then content of WorkingSet objects will be added to the WorkingSet firstWorkingSet.

        If mergeToFirst is set to false, the WorkingSet objects will be merged to the current working set.

        Set {WorkingSet objects - WorkingSet firstWorkingSet} will be deleted if deleteRemains is set to true

        Parameters:
        user -
        firstWorkingSet -
        wss -
        boolean -
        boolean -
        Returns:
        boolean

      • mergeWorkingSets

        boolean mergeWorkingSets(User user,
                       WorkingSet ws1,
                       WorkingSet ws2)
        Merge two WorkingSet objects into one.
        If WorkingSet WS1 and WorkingSet WS2 are merged, then content of WorkingSet WS2 will be added to WorkingSet WS1 and WS2 will be deleted

        Parameters:
        user -
        ws1 -
        ws2 -
        Returns:
        boolean
